600.subject: AEGD
600.courseDescription: Clinical Dentistry I. (0-0). Credit 0. Clinical diagnosis and treatment of advanced comprehensive multidisciplinary cases under faculty guidance and supervision.

601.subject: AEGD
601.courseDescription: Clinical Dentistry II. (0-0). Credit 0. Clinical diagnosis and treatment of advanced comprehensive multidisciplinary cases under faculty guidance and supervision.

602.subject: AEGD
602.courseDescription: Clinical Dentistry III. (0-0). Credit 0. Clinical diagnosis and treatment of advanced comprehensive multidisciplinary cases under faculty guidance and supervision.

603.subject: AEGD
603.courseDescription: Implant Dentistry. (1.5-0). Credit 1.5. Diagnosis, management and treatment of both fixed and removable implant patients. Lecture, seminars and patient treatment.

604.subject: AEGD
604.courseDescription: Practice Management I. Credit 0 to 1.5. All areas of practice and business management will be discussed, including office management, personnel management, professional ethics, financial planning, starting a practice, office design and legal responsibilities.

605.subject: AEGD
605.courseDescription: Practice Management II. Credit 0 to 1.5. All areas of practice and business management will be discussed, including office management, personnel management, professional ethics, financial planning, starting a practice, office design and legal responsibilities.

606.subject: AEGD
606.courseDescription: Advanced Removable Prosthodontics. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis, treatment planning and clinical treatment of complicated cases requiring advanced skills in removable prosthodontics.

607.subject: AEGD
607.courseDescription: Advanced Fixed Prosthodontics. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis, treatment planning and clinical treatment of complicated cases requiring advanced skills in fixed prosthodontics, including implant restoration.

608.subject: AEGD
608.courseDescription: Advanced Clinical Periodontics. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis, treatment planning, prognosis and instrumentation skills; basic surgical techniques.

609.subject: AEGD
609.courseDescription: Advanced Clinical Orthodontics. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis and evaluation of a variety of malocclusions; emphasis on minor tooth movement, interceptive treatment and maintenance of arch integrity.

610.subject: AEGD
610.courseDescription: Advanced Pediatric Dentistry. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis, treatment planning and clinical treatment of complex pediatric patients; emphasis on medically compromised and behavior management cases.

611.subject: AEGD
611.courseDescription: Advanced Clinical Endodontics I. Credit 2. Diagnosis, management and treatment of patients with complex endodontic problems; surgical and nonsurgical treatment and retreatment of complicated cases.

612.subject: AEGD
612.courseDescription: Advanced Geriatric Dentistry. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis, treatment planning and treatment of geriatric patients with special needs; emphasis on medically, physically and mentally compromised patients.

613.subject: AEGD
613.courseDescription: Advanced Maxillofacial Surgery. (0-0-2). Credit 2. Principles of oral surgery techniques and procedures in the outpatient clinic and operating room environments; demonstrations and clinical application.

614.subject: AEGD
614.courseTitle: ADV DENT FOR SPEC CARE PATIENT
614.courseDescription: Advanced Dentistry for Special Care Patients. Credit 1.5. Clinical application and experience in the care and treatment of special care patients with medical, physical and mental handicaps.

615.subject: AEGD
615.courseDescription: Treatment Planning Conference I. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis and treatment planning for comprehensive cases involving a multidisciplinary approach; student presentation of complex cases to a graduate faculty forum; defense of treatment plans using documented scientific or clinical evidence.

616.subject: AEGD
616.courseDescription: Treatment Planning Conference II. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis and treatment planning for comprehensive cases involving a multidisciplinary approach; student presentation of complex cases to a graduate faculty forum; defense of treatment plans using documented scientific or clinical evidence.

617.subject: AEGD
617.courseDescription: Treatment Planning Conference III. Credit 1.5. Diagnosis and treatment planning for comprehensive cases involving a multidisciplinary approach; student presentation of complex cases to a graduate faculty forum; defense of treatment plans using documented scientific or clinical evidence.

618.subject: AEGD
618.courseDescription: Current Literature Review I. Credit 1.5. Detailed review of relevant literature on topics selected by the graduate faculty and presentation by graduate students; enhancement of student knowledge in selected subject areas and development of ability to critically evaluate scientific literature.

619.courseDescription: Current Literature Review II. Credit 1.5. Detailed review of relevant literature on topics selected by the graduate faculty and presentation by graduate students; enhancement of student knowledge in selected subject areas and development of ability to critically evaluate scientific literature.

620.subject: AEGD
620.courseDescription: Current Literature Review III. Credit 1.5. Detailed review of relevant literature on topics selected by the graduate faculty and presentation by graduate students; enhancement of student knowledge in selected subject areas and development of ability to critically evaluate scientific literature.

621.subject: AEGD
621.courseDescription: Clinical Pathology I. Credit 1.5-2. Presentation and discussion of clinical cases representing various types of oral pathology of both hard and soft tissues; formulation of a logical differential diagnosis and appropriate treatment.

622.subject: AEGD
622.courseDescription: Clinical Pathology II. Credit 1.5-2. Presentation and discussion of clinical cases representing various types of oral pathology of both hard and soft tissues; formulation of a logical differential diagnosis and appropriate treatment.

623.subject: AEGD
623.courseDescription: Clinical Pathology III. Credit 1.5-2. Presentation and discussion of clinical cases representing various types of oral pathology of both hard and soft tissues; formulation of a logical differential diagnosis and appropriate treatment.

624.subject: AEGD
624.courseDescription: Ethics in Dentistry. Credit 1.5. Ethical approach to practice promotion and professional interactions.

625.subject: AEGD
625.courseDescription: Current Concepts in Operative Dentistry. Credit 1.5. Recent theories and techniques relating to restorative dental materials; emphasis on indications and contraindications for tooth-colored restorative materials; esthetic dentistry.

689.subject: AEGD
689.courseDescription: Special Topics In... Credit 0 to 4. Selected topics in an identified area of advanced education in general dentistry. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisite: Graduate classification.

691.subject: AEGD
691.courseDescription: Research. Credit 0 to 10. Research for thesis or dissertation.
